<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-01-25T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-01-25T19:00:00-05:00" n="633" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d633">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">810.796/4: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Poindexter</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-01-25T19:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">January
                                            25, 1928—7 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>6. Your 4, January 21, 1 p.m.</p>
                            <list>
                                <label>1.</label>
                                <item>The phrase “foreign interests” is intended to cover all
                                    interests in Peru not American or Peruvian.</item>
                                <label>2.</label>
                                <item>The American interests referred to in the Department’s 4,
                                    January 19, 3 p.m., are the Keystone and Huff-Daland Dusters,
                                    who are connected with Hayden Stone (Financial) and Pan American
                                    Airways, and possibly eventually others.</item>
                                <label>3.</label>
                                <item>Give all possible and proper support to Woolman.</item>
                            </list>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>